Package com.here.platform.location.core.graph.javadsl

Class FilteredGraph<V,E>

java.lang.Object
com.here.platform.location.core.graph.javadsl.FilteredGraph<V,E>
Type Parameters:
V - The Vertex type
E - The Edge type param: graph The original graph param: edgePredicate The predicate used to filter edges. Any edge for which the predicate returns false will not be part of the filtered graph.
All Implemented Interfaces:
DirectedGraph<V,E>, IncidenceGraph<V,E>
public class FilteredGraph<V,E> extends Object implements DirectedGraph<V,E>
A filtered view of a directed graph.

The filter can remove edges from a DirectedGraph using an edge predicate. Vertices are always preserved.
